g.title: The agent is deployed on the host and begins its operation.
Establishes connection to the private blockchain network.

g.text: Agent receives Lisp code deployment, logs the event
g.title: Receives and logs the deployment of Lisp code. This might include information about the vendor who deployed the code, time & date, and more.

g.text: Starts executing the code on the machine
g.title: Executes the deployed Lisp code on the machine.

g.text: If anything goes wrong, analyze the blockchain
g.title: Analyzes the blockchain logs to investigate any issues.

g.text: Trace back to the responsible party
g.title: Identifies the source of the problematic code deployment.
Generate report and submit to appropriate party (e.g. via e-mail, webhook, etc.)
